00:03:06,562 --> 00:03:07,562
Hmm.

10
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:34,964
- Yeah!
- On the 1 5th of May...

11
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:36,966
in theJungle of Nool...

12
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:39,969
in the heat ofthe day,
in the cool ofa pool...

13
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:43,556
he was splashing,
enjoying thejungle's greatjoys...

15
00:03:46,727 --> 00:03:49,645
when Horton the elephant
heard a small noise.

17
00:03:51,732 --> 00:03:53,482
Hmm?

18
00:03:55,152 --> 00:03:57,403
Hmm.

19
00:03:59,531 --> 00:04:01,532
- Horton!
- Horton!

20
00:04:03,201 --> 00:04:05,161
Good morning, class.
Are you ready?

21
00:04:05,245 --> 00:04:07,413
- Yeah!
- Jump on board!

22
00:04:07,497 --> 00:04:09,373
Look out below!

23
00:04:09,458 --> 00:04:11,292
Tommy's on board.

24
00:04:11,376 --> 00:04:13,294
Katie, you there?

25
00:04:14,338 --> 00:04:17,506
- Ahh.
- Okay.

26
00:04:18,675 --> 00:04:21,093
Shh. There it is.

27
00:04:21,178 --> 00:04:25,765
This is one ofthejungle's
most amazing creatures― the leaf bug.

28
00:04:25,849 --> 00:04:28,225
In order to protect itself
from predators...

29
00:04:28,310 --> 00:04:30,770
it disguises itselfas a leaf.

30
00:04:33,065 --> 00:04:36,025
Hmm.

31
00:04:36,109 --> 00:04:38,486
This one's got quite a grip.

32
00:04:38,570 --> 00:04:41,322
Come on, little buddy.
Don't be shy.

34
00:04:43,450 --> 00:04:45,451
I guess I was mistaken, kids.

35
00:04:46,578 --> 00:04:49,705
There are obviously
no leaf bugs in this area.

36
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:52,959
Even a prof― Aah! They're on me!

37
00:04:53,043 --> 00:04:54,794
Get 'em off!

38
00:04:54,878 --> 00:04:57,546
I think I swallowed one!

39
00:04:57,631 --> 00:05:00,132
Help me!

40
00:05:00,217 --> 00:05:02,301
- Pull it out!
- Uh, okay.

42
00:05:04,763 --> 00:05:08,265
Whoo-whoo! Whee!

43
00:05:08,392 --> 00:05:11,477
- Then humpfing a "Humpf!"
was a sour kangaroo...
- Humpf!

44
00:05:11,561 --> 00:05:14,188
the type who's convinced
she knows better than you.

45
00:05:14,272 --> 00:05:16,816
She made every law
and enforced every rule...

46
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:20,778
as self-proclaimed head of the Jungle of Nool.

47
00:05:20,862 --> 00:05:23,906
- Humpf!
- Why can't I play with the other kids, Mom?

48
00:05:23,991 --> 00:05:25,908
How many times have I told you...

49
00:05:25,993 --> 00:05:29,120
that thejungle is no place
to act like a wild animal?

52
00:05:38,714 --> 00:05:42,091
- Ooh.
- My, that Horton certainly is eccentric.

53
00:05:42,175 --> 00:05:45,094
And the children are learning
so much from him.

54
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:48,431
Learning to be a bunch
of harebrained half-wits.

55
00:05:48,515 --> 00:05:51,767
And that's why my Rudy
is pouch-schooled.

56
00:05:51,852 --> 00:05:54,687
So while Kangaroo stood there sneering a sneer―

57
00:05:54,771 --> 00:05:57,481
Horton, that was the best time I've ever had
in my life. What are you gonna show us next?

58
00:05:58,608 --> 00:06:01,777
once again
the speck floated right by Horton's ear.

59
00:06:01,862 --> 00:06:03,779
Help!

60
00:06:03,864 --> 00:06:06,699
And he heard it again,just a very faint yelp...

61
00:06:06,783 --> 00:06:09,452
as ifsome tiny person
were calling for help.

63
00:06:12,247 --> 00:06:14,498
And you know what he thought?

64
00:06:14,583 --> 00:06:18,878
Why, he thought that there must be
someone on top ofthat small speck ofdust.

65
00:06:18,962 --> 00:06:21,922
Or even a family—
it just might be so―

66
00:06:22,007 --> 00:06:24,884
a family with children
just starting to grow.

68
00:06:27,554 --> 00:06:29,680
I wanna live!

69
00:06:29,765 --> 00:06:33,309
Uh, I gotta go.
Katie, you're in charge.

70
00:06:34,478 --> 00:06:36,228
- Ahh.
- Huh?

72
00:06:38,857 --> 00:06:40,775
Wait! Come back!

73
00:06:40,859 --> 00:06:42,943
- Watch it!
- Eh— Uh—

74
00:06:43,028 --> 00:06:44,862
Ohh!

80
00:07:04,508 --> 00:07:06,801
One more! One more!

81
00:07:06,885 --> 00:07:10,429
One more! One more!
One more! One more!

83
00:07:14,142 --> 00:07:16,060
Ooh! Ooh!

84
00:07:16,144 --> 00:07:18,020
- I hear someone comin'.
- Gimme those.

85
00:07:19,397 --> 00:07:21,107
Wait!

86
00:07:21,191 --> 00:07:23,275
Sound the alarm!

87
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:26,195
Huh?

88
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:29,406
Excuse me. Pardon my stampede.

89
00:07:29,491 --> 00:07:32,743
Sorry, Wickershams. I promise
I'm gonna clean all this up later.

90
00:07:32,828 --> 00:07:34,829
Bring the ammo!

92
00:07:43,255 --> 00:07:46,215
I love the smell of bananas
in the morning!

93
00:07:47,759 --> 00:07:50,052
Banana in the hole!

94
00:07:50,137 --> 00:07:53,055
Come on, guys.
We're all mammals.

95
00:07:54,057 --> 00:07:55,724
Whoa!

96
00:07:55,809 --> 00:07:58,561
I feel the diplomatic
process is beginning to break down.

97
00:07:58,645 --> 00:08:00,938
Whoa!

98
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:04,233
There you are! I got ya!

99
00:08:07,904 --> 00:08:09,947
- Hi, kids.
- Whoa!
- Aah!

104
00:08:23,420 --> 00:08:26,881
There. Now you're safe.

105
00:08:26,965 --> 00:08:30,676
I know I heard you say something.

106
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:32,970
I just know it.

107
00:08:33,054 --> 00:08:35,556
Where are you?

109
00:08:39,895 --> 00:08:42,605
Humpf!

110
00:08:42,689 --> 00:08:44,940
- Horton!
- Oh. Sorry.

111
00:08:45,025 --> 00:08:47,276
Uh—
I just—

112
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:49,361
There was this speck, and, uh...

113
00:08:49,446 --> 00:08:51,405
it called out for help.

114
00:08:51,489 --> 00:08:53,866
- And I was—
- The speck called out for help?

115
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:55,868
Well, not the speck.

116
00:08:55,952 --> 00:08:57,870
I mean, that's... ridiculous.

117
00:08:57,954 --> 00:09:01,165
Is that what you thought I meant? No.

118
00:09:01,249 --> 00:09:04,501
The speck can't call out for help.
Come on. Get real.

120
00:09:06,588 --> 00:09:10,841
No, there's a tiny person on that speck
that needs my help.

121
00:09:10,926 --> 00:09:12,718
Absurd.

122
00:09:12,802 --> 00:09:14,720
There aren't people that small.

123
00:09:14,804 --> 00:09:17,389
Well, maybe they aren't small.

124
00:09:17,474 --> 00:09:19,391
Maybe... we're big.

125
00:09:19,476 --> 00:09:21,393
- Horton—
- No, really. Think about it.

126
00:09:21,478 --> 00:09:25,064
What ifthere were someone
way out there...

127
00:09:25,148 --> 00:09:27,399
looking down on our world right now?

128
00:09:27,484 --> 00:09:29,401
And to them, we're the specks.

129
00:09:29,486 --> 00:09:33,197
And then maybe someone else will come along
and say, "There can't be people that small."

130
00:09:33,281 --> 00:09:36,533
And the first guy would say,
"Are you calling me a liar?"

131
00:09:36,618 --> 00:09:39,036
And the second guy would say,
"Ifthe shoe fits, wear it!"

132
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:41,538
Now the fists are flying.
The first guy picks up a brick―

133
00:09:41,623 --> 00:09:44,959
You might want to zip up the pouch
for this next part— "Fat boy, you want some?"

134
00:09:45,043 --> 00:09:46,961
- Horton!
- What?

135
00:09:47,045 --> 00:09:49,296
There is nothing on that speck.

136
00:09:50,507 --> 00:09:52,424
- But I heard.
- Did you?

137
00:09:52,509 --> 00:09:55,344
Really?
Oh, my.

138
00:09:55,428 --> 00:09:59,014
Then how come / don't hear anything?

139
00:09:59,099 --> 00:10:01,350
Well—

140
00:10:01,434 --> 00:10:05,521
If you can't see,
hear or feel something...

141
00:10:05,605 --> 00:10:07,523
it doesn't exist.

142
00:10:07,607 --> 00:10:13,487
And believing in tiny, imaginary people
is just not something we do...

143
00:10:13,571 --> 00:10:17,157
or tolerate here
in the Jungle of Nool.

144
00:10:17,242 --> 00:10:21,996
Really? 'Cause I bet if I tried, I could find
somebody who'd believe what I was saying.

145
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,998
You will do nothing ofthe sort.

146
00:10:24,082 --> 00:10:26,667
You will not breathe a word ofthis lie
to anyone else...

147
00:10:26,751 --> 00:10:28,669
especially the children.

148
00:10:28,753 --> 00:10:32,756
I do not want you poisoning their minds
with this nonsense.

149
00:10:32,841 --> 00:10:35,926
Our community has standards, Horton.

150
00:10:36,011 --> 00:10:40,389
Ifyou want to remain a part of it,
l recommend you follow them.

151
00:10:41,474 --> 00:10:43,809
Mmm. Have a nice day.

153
00:10:46,896 --> 00:10:50,149
All right then.
I'll, uh, take that under advisement.

154
00:10:50,233 --> 00:10:52,526
Certainly appreciate your input.

156
00:10:54,904 --> 00:10:56,822
I don't understand.

157
00:10:56,906 --> 00:11:00,701
I know I heard you.
It was as plain as the nose on my face.

158
00:11:01,703 --> 00:11:03,620
That's it.

159
00:11:03,705 --> 00:11:05,622
Maybe you can't hear me.

160
00:11:05,707 --> 00:11:08,625
Ofcourse.
Your ears must be tiny.

161
00:11:08,710 --> 00:11:10,794
I need to speak up.

163
00:11:12,881 --> 00:11:15,507
Hello!

164
00:11:15,592 --> 00:11:18,510
Now, some people out there― I think  l know who―

165
00:11:18,595 --> 00:11:21,138
may find they agree
with that sour kangaroo.

166
00:11:22,349 --> 00:11:25,559
There can't really be people
as small as a mite.

167
00:11:25,643 --> 00:11:30,022
Well, there can and there are,
because Horton was right.

169
00:11:39,491 --> 00:11:43,160
Hello!

170
00:11:45,497 --> 00:11:48,415
That single "hello"
traveled all the way down...

171
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:50,417
through the speck,
through the clouds...

172
00:11:50,502 --> 00:11:53,253
till it found a small town.

173
00:11:53,338 --> 00:11:56,507
A town known as Who-ville,
for there lived the Whos...

174
00:11:56,591 --> 00:11:59,927
feeling happy and safe,
knowing only good news...

175
00:12:00,011 --> 00:12:03,514
unaware that theirworld
was a speck on a clover...

176
00:12:03,598 --> 00:12:06,225
unaware that the sweet life they knew
might be over.

177
00:12:06,309 --> 00:12:08,018
- Over.
- Under.

178
00:12:08,103 --> 00:12:10,020
Oi! Oi! Oi!

180
00:12:12,107 --> 00:12:14,858
The Mayor of Who-ville, a man named McDodd...

181
00:12:14,943 --> 00:12:17,861
was devoted and fair
and a little bit odd.

186
00:12:34,879 --> 00:12:38,382
The mayor and his wife,
they had children to spare―

187
00:12:38,466 --> 00:12:42,761
96 daughters,
some here and some there.

188
00:12:42,846 --> 00:12:46,765
Ninety-six girls to love.
Ninety-six girls to teach.

189
00:12:46,850 --> 00:12:51,645
But the mayor had only a few seconds for each.

190
00:12:51,729 --> 00:12:54,982
Daddy, I got better than best
on my "Who-story" test.

191
00:12:55,066 --> 00:12:56,984
Ah, Who-story.
I remember it well.

192
00:12:57,068 --> 00:13:00,028
- That's one of my girls.
- Hildy's been using my hairbrush!

193
00:13:00,113 --> 00:13:02,114
Holly's been using my hairbrush!

194
00:13:02,198 --> 00:13:04,158
Look! Over there!

195
00:13:04,242 --> 00:13:06,201
There. All better.

196
00:13:06,286 --> 00:13:08,328
Can I please have a Who-phone, Dad?

197
00:13:08,413 --> 00:13:10,330
Everyone else in my class has one.

198
00:13:10,415 --> 00:13:12,082
Oh, really? Everyone?

199
00:13:15,545 --> 00:13:17,379
Oh. I will think about it.

200
00:13:17,464 --> 00:13:19,381
Daddy, look! Daddy, look!

202
00:13:21,342 --> 00:13:23,927
Mm-hmm.

203
00:13:24,012 --> 00:13:25,596
Toof!

204
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:27,389
It's a "T-H," sweetheart.
It's "tooth."

205
00:13:27,682 --> 00:13:30,309
In Who-ville tradition, unlike yours or mine...

206
00:13:30,393 --> 00:13:33,187
the mayor's oldest is next
in the mayoral line.

207
00:13:33,271 --> 00:13:35,814
And who was the oldest,
to lead and stand tall?

208
00:13:35,899 --> 00:13:38,775
It wasJoJo, his son,
the smallest Who ofall.

209
00:13:38,860 --> 00:13:41,153
So,JoJo, what's, uh—
What's shakin'?

210
00:13:41,237 --> 00:13:44,615
What's happenin'?
What's the word?

211
00:13:44,741 --> 00:13:47,659
Now, to you or to me, it's abundantly clear...

212
00:13:47,744 --> 00:13:50,913
that JoJo did not want
his father's career.

213
00:13:50,997 --> 00:13:53,916
But the mayor pressed forward,
completely deluded...

214
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,918
Boom-badda, boom-badda,
bidda-bidda-boom!

215
00:13:56,002 --> 00:14:00,380
whileJoJojust sat there
in silence and brooded.

217
00:14:03,635 --> 00:14:05,135
Oh,JoJo.

218
00:14:05,220 --> 00:14:08,013
- Why does he get more time?
- That's not fair.

219
00:14:08,097 --> 00:14:10,390
Son. Hey.

220
00:14:10,475 --> 00:14:12,559
And why didn't he speak?

221
00:14:12,644 --> 00:14:16,730
Well, I think that the lad was afraid,
if he did, he might let down his dad.

222
00:14:16,814 --> 00:14:18,732
You know what's awesome?

223
00:14:18,816 --> 00:14:21,109
This is awesome.

224
00:14:21,194 --> 00:14:25,948
Just look at the men and women
hanging on these walls.

225
00:14:26,032 --> 00:14:29,618
You, my boy, are part
ofa family legacy...

226
00:14:29,702 --> 00:14:31,995
that spans centuries.

227
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:33,997
You know what?

228
00:14:34,082 --> 00:14:38,001
Your grandfather was mayor
of Who-ville. Mm-hmm.

229
00:14:38,086 --> 00:14:41,213
And your great-grandmother.

230
00:14:41,297 --> 00:14:42,965
That's right.

231
00:14:43,049 --> 00:14:45,467
All the way down to your―

232
00:14:45,552 --> 00:14:47,844
great-

233
00:14:47,929 --> 00:14:50,222
great-great-great-

234
00:14:50,306 --> 00:14:52,474
not-so-great-
great-great-

235
00:14:52,559 --> 00:14:56,395
great-great-great-
great-great-great-great-

237
00:15:01,359 --> 00:15:04,695
Someday, I hope to join them...

238
00:15:04,779 --> 00:15:06,697
be one ofthe greats.

239
00:15:06,781 --> 00:15:10,993
I tell you, JoJo,
there is nothing like being mayor.

240
00:15:11,077 --> 00:15:15,289
I get to sign resolutions,
approve ordinances, submit budgets.

241
00:15:15,373 --> 00:15:19,960
And in the Edible Parade, I'm the one
sitting on top ofthe giant meatball.

242
00:15:21,588 --> 00:15:25,882
Someday, that can be you too,JoJo.

243
00:15:25,967 --> 00:15:31,638
Someday, you'll be the one
wearing the mayoral crest.

244
00:15:31,723 --> 00:15:36,768
You just—
You just need to—

245
00:15:36,853 --> 00:15:38,854
You know what I mean?

246
00:15:39,856 --> 00:15:42,149
Okay. Good chat.

247
00:15:42,233 --> 00:15:46,528
I'm glad that we had this talk...

248
00:15:47,530 --> 00:15:50,907
that l'm continuing now by myself.

249
00:15:50,992 --> 00:15:53,076
Good.

251
00:15:55,413 --> 00:15:57,706
Huh.

252
00:15:57,874 --> 00:16:01,043
Ooh. There. That oughta be comfy.

254
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:07,299
Nothing wrong with this, Morton.

255
00:16:07,383 --> 00:16:09,509
Nothin' wrong with this.

256
00:16:09,594 --> 00:16:14,931
Just you and me and the speck shootin' the breeze.

257
00:16:15,016 --> 00:16:17,225
- We're a club. We're a group.
- Hmm?

258
00:16:17,310 --> 00:16:19,227
We can take a vote on the issues.

259
00:16:19,312 --> 00:16:22,856
We can be a secret society that controls
the balance of power in the world.

260
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:26,026
- Horton—
- And no one else can join
unless they wear funny hats.

263
00:16:30,198 --> 00:16:33,742
- Listen, Horton—
- The chair recognizes Brother Morton.

264
00:16:33,826 --> 00:16:37,913
I am really happy
you found this speck and all...

265
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:42,334
but you might wanna think
about keeping it to yourself.

266
00:16:42,418 --> 00:16:44,419
Hmm? What? Why?

267
00:16:45,672 --> 00:16:48,924
You're talking to a clover.
That doesn't look good.

268
00:16:51,511 --> 00:16:53,595
You know what doesn't look good?

269
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:56,890
You talking about the speck
like the speck isn't even there.

270
00:16:56,974 --> 00:16:59,810
The speck never said
anything bad about you.

271
00:16:59,894 --> 00:17:03,021
But, hey, good luck
with your illusion ofsuperiority.

272
00:17:03,106 --> 00:17:07,401
You know, the speck can think anything
it wants about me. It's a speck.

273
00:17:07,485 --> 00:17:09,403
Whoa!

274
00:17:09,487 --> 00:17:11,697
I see what's going on here.

275
00:17:11,781 --> 00:17:15,534
Morton, no matter how tight
the speck and I get...

276
00:17:15,618 --> 00:17:18,412
the speck could never replace you.

277
00:17:18,496 --> 00:17:21,748
I'm only sad that I would have
to explain that at this point.

278
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:26,420
Well, that's awesome, Horton.
That really helps.

279
00:17:26,504 --> 00:17:29,214
Just try to keep this to yourself.

280
00:17:29,298 --> 00:17:31,216
I'll see you later.

281
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:33,260
Try.

282
00:17:33,344 --> 00:17:35,345
Hmm.

283
00:17:36,514 --> 00:17:39,391
Hey, Horton. What you got there?

284
00:17:39,475 --> 00:17:41,476
What? Nothing.

285
00:17:41,561 --> 00:17:43,478
We're not doing anything.

286
00:17:43,563 --> 00:17:46,189
We're totally alone.

287
00:17:46,274 --> 00:17:49,192
- Who's "we"?
- We? What? We? Did I say that?

288
00:17:49,277 --> 00:17:52,571
No, I would never say that, because that
would imply that I was with someone...

289
00:17:52,655 --> 00:17:55,240
and not alone.

291
00:18:00,455 --> 00:18:03,165
Okay, seriously, you can't tell anybody.
I mean it.

292
00:18:03,249 --> 00:18:07,002
Ifanybody finds out about this,
it could be very, very bad.

293
00:18:08,129 --> 00:18:10,297
I'm not sure why.

294
00:18:10,381 --> 00:18:12,299
We won't tell anyone.

295
00:18:12,383 --> 00:18:15,844
And ifwe do, we'll tell them
not to tell anyone.

296
00:18:15,928 --> 00:18:17,763
Perfect.

297
00:18:17,847 --> 00:18:19,765
Okay, I'm taking a bath, right?

298
00:18:19,849 --> 00:18:22,184
'Cause my skin
gets kind ofdry and ashy―

299
00:18:22,268 --> 00:18:24,478
While Horton came clean
about the speck that he'd found...

300
00:18:24,562 --> 00:18:26,646
and how he saved it
when it nearly drowned...

301
00:18:26,731 --> 00:18:28,648
the mayor set off
on his morning commute...

302
00:18:28,733 --> 00:18:32,194
and noticed things weren't
quite the same on his route.

303
00:18:32,278 --> 00:18:34,738
But please don't blame Horton,
for he didn't know...

304
00:18:34,822 --> 00:18:37,115
that a small bump above―

305
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:40,118
And I dove into the water like this!

306
00:18:40,203 --> 00:18:43,330
was a big bump below.

307
00:18:43,414 --> 00:18:45,832
Hey,Joe. Don't work too hard.

308
00:18:45,917 --> 00:18:48,835
Ah, these luxury condos,
they don't build themselves.

310
00:18:53,007 --> 00:18:56,301
Hey, look at that!
I guess they do build themselves.

311
00:18:56,385 --> 00:18:59,888
Okay, that happened.

312
00:19:02,350 --> 00:19:05,435
Now, the mayor knew it was hisjob to convey...

313
00:19:05,520 --> 00:19:07,729
the unusual things
that he'd noticed that day.

314
00:19:07,814 --> 00:19:11,066
But there was one problem.
Though his will was strong—

315
00:19:11,150 --> 00:19:13,693
- You're late.
- Thankyou, Miss Yelp.

316
00:19:13,778 --> 00:19:16,905
nothing in Who-ville had ever gone wrong.

317
00:19:16,989 --> 00:19:20,492
We have all that we need.
We need all that we've got.

318
00:19:20,576 --> 00:19:24,246
We like it in Who-ville.
We like it a lot!

319
00:19:24,330 --> 00:19:28,542
We're all very busy
with the Who-centennial coming up...

320
00:19:28,626 --> 00:19:31,545
so let's bring this meeting to order.

321
00:19:31,629 --> 00:19:36,466
Mr. Mayor, I presume
you have some good news for us.

322
00:19:36,551 --> 00:19:38,677
Well, it's news.

323
00:19:38,761 --> 00:19:42,556
I don't know ifwe need to go labeling it
good or bad or anything like that.

324
00:19:42,640 --> 00:19:46,685
The thing is,
I have noticed some odd goings-on...

325
00:19:46,769 --> 00:19:48,687
in Who-ville lately.

326
00:19:48,771 --> 00:19:50,689
Good odd goings-on?

327
00:19:50,773 --> 00:19:54,025
Well, you know, tremors,
clouds swirling in the sky.

328
00:19:54,110 --> 00:19:57,028
It seems to me,just to be safe,
we might want to consider...

329
00:19:57,113 --> 00:19:59,531
postponing the Who-centennial.

330
00:19:59,615 --> 00:20:03,118
- Consider what?
- Postponing the Who-centennial.

331
00:20:04,620 --> 00:20:07,205
What? Speak up, man!

332
00:20:07,290 --> 00:20:10,584
Postponing the Who-centennial. All right?

337
00:20:29,604 --> 00:20:31,187
Hmm.

338
00:20:31,272 --> 00:20:36,192
We are about to celebrate 100 years
of Who-ville happiness and harmony...

339
00:20:36,277 --> 00:20:38,904
and you want
to postpone the celebration?

340
00:20:38,988 --> 00:20:40,906
Well, what ifWho-ville's not safe?

341
00:20:40,990 --> 00:20:43,116
Nothing ever goes wrong
in Who-ville.

342
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:47,495
Never has and never will.
You blathering boob.

343
00:20:47,580 --> 00:20:49,998
Boob?

345
00:20:53,711 --> 00:20:55,879
The Who-centennial
will proceed as planned.

346
00:20:55,963 --> 00:20:59,507
The mayor was merely being an idiot.

347
00:20:59,592 --> 00:21:03,011
It will be all smiles from now on.

348
00:21:04,513 --> 00:21:07,933
Ow. Ow.

349
00:21:08,184 --> 00:21:11,937
Girl, I got 15,000 friends already.

350
00:21:12,021 --> 00:21:16,107
What you mean it don't look like me?
That look just like me.

351
00:21:16,192 --> 00:21:19,319
Ten years ago.
Wait a minute. Hold on for a second.

352
00:21:22,949 --> 00:21:26,201
Treats me like an idiot.
I am not an idiot.

353
00:21:28,371 --> 00:21:31,289
Do I look like an idiot?

354
00:21:31,374 --> 00:21:35,502
- You don't want me to answer that.
- I am not an idiot.

355
00:21:35,586 --> 00:21:40,131
Has the nerve to call me a boob? I would never
call somebody a boob. He's a boob.

356
00:21:40,216 --> 00:21:43,635
Look at you. Yuck.

357
00:21:43,719 --> 00:21:45,637
Look at your face.

358
00:21:45,721 --> 00:21:49,391
And l bet you don't look so good
with a stapler in your head!

360
00:21:58,901 --> 00:22:01,945
Whoa! Whoa!

361
00:22:02,029 --> 00:22:04,364
Ow. Ow. Ow.

362
00:22:04,448 --> 00:22:07,701
- Yaah! Thankyou, Miss Yelp.
- You're welcome.

363
00:22:07,785 --> 00:22:09,786
Oh!

364
00:22:09,870 --> 00:22:11,955
- Hello?
- Who said that?

365
00:22:12,039 --> 00:22:14,582
I'll punch you!
Whoa!

367
00:22:18,087 --> 00:22:20,005
Hmm?

369
00:22:23,926 --> 00:22:25,760
Hello?

370
00:22:25,845 --> 00:22:27,762
Hello.

371
00:22:27,847 --> 00:22:30,181
Hello.

373
00:22:37,273 --> 00:22:40,442
- Who's there?
- Um, this is the mayor.

374
00:22:40,526 --> 00:22:43,778
The mayor? The mayor?

375
00:22:43,863 --> 00:22:47,032
I'm talking to the mayor!

376
00:22:47,116 --> 00:22:51,494
I knew it, I knew it,  l knew it!
I knew there was life on this speck.

377
00:22:51,579 --> 00:22:53,872
Speck? What speck?

378
00:22:53,956 --> 00:22:59,127
Well, um, I don't exactly know
how to tell you this, but...

379
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:02,047
you're living on a speck.

380
00:23:02,131 --> 00:23:06,718
Well, I hate to disagree with you,
O Voice from the Drainpipe...

381
00:23:06,802 --> 00:23:09,054
but I live in Who-ville.

382
00:23:09,138 --> 00:23:11,097
Well, then Who-ville's a speck.

383
00:23:11,182 --> 00:23:13,099
Right. Okay.

384
00:23:13,184 --> 00:23:15,560
Seriously, who is this?

385
00:23:15,644 --> 00:23:17,562
Is this Burt from Accounting?

386
00:23:17,646 --> 00:23:21,608
Uh, no. This is Horton.
I'm an elephant.

387
00:23:21,692 --> 00:23:27,155
Okay, Horton— fake name—
where are you?

388
00:23:27,239 --> 00:23:29,741
Well, from where you're standing...

389
00:23:29,825 --> 00:23:33,411
I guess I'm in the sky.

390
00:23:33,496 --> 00:23:37,082
Compared to you, I'm enormous, which is saying
something, because I've slimmed down a bit.

391
00:23:37,166 --> 00:23:39,084
I swim.

392
00:23:39,168 --> 00:23:43,755
Your whole world
fits on a flower in my world.

393
00:23:43,839 --> 00:23:46,800
Oh, man, this is even
pushing it foryou, Burt.

394
00:23:46,884 --> 00:23:50,011
Don't believe me? Watch what happens
when I put you in the shade.

395
00:23:50,096 --> 00:23:52,347
This is absolutely impossibl—

396
00:23:52,431 --> 00:23:53,681
Dark.

397
00:23:53,766 --> 00:23:58,186
Light. Dark. Light.

398
00:23:58,270 --> 00:24:01,606
Dark. Light. Dark. Light. Dark. Light.
Dark. Light. Dark. Light. Dark.

399
00:24:01,690 --> 00:24:04,317
- Light.
- Whoo.

400
00:24:04,401 --> 00:24:10,281
Don't you see? We're in the middle of
some kind ofamazing cosmic convergence.

401
00:24:10,366 --> 00:24:12,867
Two vastly different worlds...

402
00:24:12,952 --> 00:24:15,370
- miraculously crossing paths.
- Who— Who—

403
00:24:15,454 --> 00:24:18,123
Mine colossal!
Yours minuscule.

404
00:24:18,207 --> 00:24:21,042
Yet somehow
we've managed to make contact.

405
00:24:21,127 --> 00:24:24,379
Ifyou think about it,
it's pretty amazing.

406
00:24:26,715 --> 00:24:29,217
Is everything okay down there?

407
00:24:29,301 --> 00:24:32,220
Uh, I-I don't know.

408
00:24:32,304 --> 00:24:35,807
You tell me.
You're the one holding the speck.

409
00:24:35,891 --> 00:24:37,976
I'm the one holding the speck.

410
00:24:38,060 --> 00:24:41,020
I'm the one holding the speck.

411
00:24:41,105 --> 00:24:42,981
Don't you worry, Mr. Mayor.

412
00:24:43,065 --> 00:24:46,568
Um, hold, please.

413
00:24:46,735 --> 00:24:48,778
Oh! Ohh!

414
00:24:48,863 --> 00:24:52,115
What did all ofthis mean? The mayor hadn't a clue.

415
00:24:52,199 --> 00:24:55,076
So he ran to the office of Dr. Larue...

416
00:24:55,161 --> 00:24:57,662
the brainiest brain
on the staffat Who U.

417
00:24:57,746 --> 00:24:59,664
Dr. Larue?

418
00:24:59,748 --> 00:25:02,500
Oh, this is crazy.

419
00:25:02,585 --> 00:25:04,711
Oh. Mr. Mayor.

420
00:25:04,795 --> 00:25:06,963
Uh, how may I be ofassistance?

421
00:25:07,047 --> 00:25:09,966
I don't know.
Hey, I wasjust wondering...

422
00:25:10,050 --> 00:25:13,761
ifourworld were, say, a tiny speck, mmm,
floating through space...

423
00:25:13,846 --> 00:25:15,763
how would we know?

424
00:25:15,848 --> 00:25:17,891
Why would you ask
something like that?

425
00:25:17,975 --> 00:25:19,934
Oh, no reason.
No reason at all.

426
00:25:20,019 --> 00:25:23,313
I don't even remember.
Yes, I do. You know what?

427
00:25:23,397 --> 00:25:25,148
Some guy was talking to me.

428
00:25:25,232 --> 00:25:28,401
Not an elephant in the sky,
a guy on the ground.

429
00:25:28,485 --> 00:25:30,403
There would be several ramifications.

430
00:25:30,487 --> 00:25:32,989
Good ramifications?

431
00:25:33,073 --> 00:25:35,325
A tiny speck.

432
00:25:35,409 --> 00:25:37,160
Uh-huh, yeah. Tiny speck.

433
00:25:37,244 --> 00:25:39,746
- Floating around.
- Whoa.

434
00:25:39,830 --> 00:25:42,999
Well, we'd have
"unexplicable" tremors...

435
00:25:43,083 --> 00:25:45,543
dramatic changes in the weather.

436
00:25:45,628 --> 00:25:50,048
And ifwe didn't eventually achieve
some sort ofstability...

437
00:25:50,132 --> 00:25:52,342
our world would be...

438
00:25:52,426 --> 00:25:54,344
destroyed.

439
00:25:54,428 --> 00:25:57,597
Destroyed? Destroyed.
Oh, destroyed.

440
00:25:57,681 --> 00:26:00,433
The drama!

441
00:26:00,559 --> 00:26:03,144
Aaaah!

442
00:26:03,229 --> 00:26:07,440
- Horton.
- Uh, no, uh, this is, uh, Benny.

443
00:26:07,524 --> 00:26:10,568
Horton is busy right now.

444
00:26:10,653 --> 00:26:12,654
I'm joking.

445
00:26:12,738 --> 00:26:14,656
That's me.

446
00:26:14,740 --> 00:26:16,658
Oh, we're doomed.

447
00:26:16,742 --> 00:26:20,328
Listen, Horton,
turns out l need your help a little bit.

448
00:26:20,412 --> 00:26:23,331
Apparently, ifthat speck
keeps moving around...

449
00:26:23,415 --> 00:26:25,583
our whole world could be obliterated.

450
00:26:25,668 --> 00:26:30,672
So I need you to find us Whos
a safer, more stable home.

451
00:26:30,756 --> 00:26:32,674
And fast.

452
00:26:32,758 --> 00:26:36,469
No problem, Mr. Mayor.
Let's see.

453
00:26:36,553 --> 00:26:40,890
Mmm. Wow!
That's a nice view.

454
00:26:43,560 --> 00:26:45,603
Hello? Is everything okay?

455
00:26:45,688 --> 00:26:47,647
Ooh!

459
00:26:54,655 --> 00:26:56,489
What's going on up there?

463
00:27:04,290 --> 00:27:06,708
Oh, no!

464
00:27:07,584 --> 00:27:09,919
Aaah!

465
00:27:10,004 --> 00:27:15,008
This entire jungle
is a house of death!

466
00:27:15,092 --> 00:27:17,760
Oh, wait.
There's a good spot.

467
00:27:17,845 --> 00:27:21,139
And it's then Horton saw,
at the top of Mount Nool...

468
00:27:21,223 --> 00:27:24,434
a small cave that looked peaceful
and quiet and cool...

469
00:27:24,518 --> 00:27:27,478
where a sunflower grew
proud and tall from the ground.

470
00:27:27,563 --> 00:27:31,566
There he knew every Who
would be safe, would be sound.

471
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:35,695
I've found it, Mayor.
The perfect place.

472
00:27:35,779 --> 00:27:37,697
Right up there.

473
00:27:37,781 --> 00:27:39,866
On the top of Mount Nool.

474
00:27:39,950 --> 00:27:41,868
- Mr. Mayor?
- I wish you could—

475
00:27:41,952 --> 00:27:45,496
Oh, how shiny.

476
00:27:45,581 --> 00:27:48,916
The Who-centennial committee
is waiting foryou...

477
00:27:49,001 --> 00:27:51,919
to look over the giant meatball
for the Edible Parade.

478
00:27:52,004 --> 00:27:55,256
Oh, and then you're due at the dentist
foryour Who-root canal.

479
00:27:55,341 --> 00:27:58,968
You know, sticking "Who" in front
ofeverything doesn't make it hurt less.

480
00:27:59,053 --> 00:28:01,095
Just wastes time!

481
00:28:01,180 --> 00:28:03,473
I don't... wanna go.

482
00:28:03,599 --> 00:28:05,808
Listen, Horton, I've gotta go.

483
00:28:05,893 --> 00:28:08,811
Apparently there's a problem
with the giant meatball.

484
00:28:08,896 --> 00:28:11,814
You just take care
ofthat meatball, sir...

485
00:28:11,899 --> 00:28:14,275
and leave the freaking out to me.

486
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:17,445
So then Horton began his long, perilous trek...

487
00:28:17,529 --> 00:28:21,449
determined to save
the small world on the speck.

488
00:28:21,533 --> 00:28:23,951
Horton was faithful
and stalwart and kind.

489
00:28:24,036 --> 00:28:26,120
I got ya. Don't worry.

490
00:28:26,205 --> 00:28:28,164
He was a brave hero―

491
00:28:28,248 --> 00:28:30,750
- I'll protect you.
- at least in his mind.

492
00:28:30,834 --> 00:28:33,127
We must become invisible,
travel silently...

493
00:28:33,212 --> 00:28:36,464
for there are forces
that would seek to destroy us.

494
00:28:41,929 --> 00:28:45,056
Huh? So you think
you can sneak up on me, huh?

496
00:28:47,309 --> 00:28:50,436
It is clear that you are no match
for my technique! Hey!

498
00:28:53,273 --> 00:28:55,817
l see you have mastered
the Way ofthe Snapping Branch.

499
00:28:55,901 --> 00:28:58,903
Watch me tumble!

500
00:28:58,987 --> 00:29:00,571
Morton Mouse, go!

501
00:29:00,656 --> 00:29:03,783
You are fast, Horton,
but the kangaroo has monkeys!

502
00:29:03,867 --> 00:29:06,786
I will make monkeys ofthese monkeys!
lt is their destiny― Huh?

503
00:29:06,870 --> 00:29:09,330
My clover!

504
00:29:09,415 --> 00:29:11,416
Ooh!

505
00:29:11,500 --> 00:29:14,001
Horton is the greatest hero
ofthem all! Ha!

506
00:29:14,086 --> 00:29:16,671
- Horton! Go!
- Morton! Go!

508
00:29:18,757 --> 00:29:21,843
- But Mount Nool is that way!
- Ha-ha-ha!

509
00:29:21,927 --> 00:29:25,012
To the top of Mount Nool!
As fast as lightning! Away I go!

511
00:29:27,224 --> 00:29:29,767
Oh. Sorry, little fella.

512
00:29:29,852 --> 00:29:33,521
You'll be fine.
Just think healing thoughts.

513
00:29:36,692 --> 00:29:38,943
- Horton! Horton! Look!
- Look, look, look!

515
00:29:41,238 --> 00:29:44,574
- We've all got our own clovers
with worlds on them.
- Yeah.

516
00:29:44,658 --> 00:29:46,868
Oh.

517
00:29:46,952 --> 00:29:49,829
In my world, everyone's a pony...

518
00:29:49,913 --> 00:29:53,541
and they all eat rainbows
and poop butterflies.

519
00:29:54,918 --> 00:29:56,878
That's beautiful, Katie.

520
00:29:58,755 --> 00:30:00,756
Ahh.

521
00:30:01,758 --> 00:30:03,676
In a really weird way.

522
00:30:03,760 --> 00:30:05,636
My world is called Jessica-land.

523
00:30:05,721 --> 00:30:08,639
Everyone worships Queen Jessica
becauseJessica is so beautiful.

524
00:30:08,724 --> 00:30:11,225
Jessica, that was awesome.

526
00:30:13,061 --> 00:30:15,104
Hmm.

527
00:30:16,064 --> 00:30:17,982
- Rudy!
- Mom, be careful!

528
00:30:18,066 --> 00:30:20,985
- My best friend, Thidwick, lives on that.
- Rudy, no one lives on this.

529
00:30:21,069 --> 00:30:22,987
It's not possible.

530
00:30:23,071 --> 00:30:24,989
That Horton is a menace.

531
00:30:25,073 --> 00:30:28,826
- M-Mom, you're so weird. Don't do this to me.
- Honey, go to your room.

532
00:30:28,911 --> 00:30:31,704
Horton!

533
00:30:31,788 --> 00:30:33,956
Whee!

534
00:30:34,041 --> 00:30:36,626
- It's good!
- What do you thinkyou're doing?

535
00:30:36,710 --> 00:30:38,878
Huh? You guys with worlds
are in trouble.

536
00:30:38,962 --> 00:30:40,880
Have you forgotten
what we discussed?

537
00:30:40,964 --> 00:30:43,174
Oh, no. l'm an elephant.

538
00:30:43,258 --> 00:30:45,718
And elephants never forget.
It's a curse really.

539
00:30:45,802 --> 00:30:49,013
I was on my head, and you said "Humpf!"
I looked up, you said "What are you doing?"

540
00:30:49,097 --> 00:30:52,433
I said the thing about the speck. Then you
pulled my ears, poked me on the forehead—

541
00:30:52,518 --> 00:30:54,727
- Horton!
- Well, you did.

542
00:30:54,811 --> 00:30:58,272
Give me that clover, Horton. Now.

543
00:30:59,274 --> 00:31:02,652
No.

544
00:31:02,736 --> 00:31:04,904
No?

545
00:31:04,988 --> 00:31:07,490
Yeah.

546
00:31:07,574 --> 00:31:10,993
Are you sure you wanna
fight this fight, Horton?

547
00:31:11,078 --> 00:31:15,665
Because I promise you
it will get very ugly very fast.

548
00:31:15,749 --> 00:31:17,792
And you need to askyourself...

549
00:31:17,876 --> 00:31:21,712
"Do I really want
to put myselfthrough all this...

550
00:31:21,797 --> 00:31:23,798
for a clover?"

551
00:31:23,882 --> 00:31:28,636
Take it from me, Horton—you don't.
So hand it over.

552
00:31:32,766 --> 00:31:35,393
No! I can't give it to you.

553
00:31:35,477 --> 00:31:37,395
There are people on this speck.

554
00:31:37,479 --> 00:31:39,397
Granted, they're very small people...

555
00:31:39,481 --> 00:31:42,233
but a person's a person,
no matter how small.

556
00:31:42,317 --> 00:31:44,777
- Huh.
- How—

558
00:31:47,239 --> 00:31:49,156
You just crossed the line, Horton...

559
00:31:49,241 --> 00:31:51,909
and I'm gonna make you pay.

561
00:31:54,288 --> 00:31:57,206
Uh— Uh— Ohh!

562
00:31:57,291 --> 00:31:59,250
That Horton is a menace.

563
00:31:59,334 --> 00:32:03,671
He has those kids using their imaginations.
It's sick!

564
00:32:03,797 --> 00:32:07,842
All right, I gotta get this speck up to the top
of Mount Nool A.S.A.P.—

565
00:32:07,926 --> 00:32:09,844
whatever that means.

566
00:32:09,928 --> 00:32:12,346
Probably,
"Act swiftly, awesome pachyderm."

