00:32:12,431 --> 00:32:14,890
I mean, how hard can that be?

568
00:32:20,355 --> 00:32:25,192
It'sjust a straight plummet to certain death.

569
00:32:26,236 --> 00:32:30,531
This looks kind of... precarious.

570
00:32:30,616 --> 00:32:33,200
Well, no need to worry.

571
00:32:33,285 --> 00:32:35,202
Obviously, when they
build a bridge like this...

572
00:32:35,287 --> 00:32:38,706
they take into account
that elephants will be crossing here.

573
00:32:39,833 --> 00:32:41,751
All right. Feels good.

574
00:32:41,835 --> 00:32:43,753
I'll just get...

575
00:32:43,837 --> 00:32:46,547
the... feel of it!

577
00:32:50,344 --> 00:32:52,928
Yike!

580
00:33:03,649 --> 00:33:05,441
Oh, that's― that's true.

584
00:33:12,491 --> 00:33:14,784
All right!

585
00:33:14,868 --> 00:33:17,953
Hello. And how are we today,
Mr. Mayor?

586
00:33:19,623 --> 00:33:21,707
Say "ahh."

587
00:33:22,751 --> 00:33:24,418
Ahh.

588
00:33:25,420 --> 00:33:27,588
Aaah!

589
00:33:29,966 --> 00:33:32,468
Hmm.

590
00:33:32,552 --> 00:33:34,553
Rinse, please.

591
00:33:37,391 --> 00:33:41,435
Huh. I think a few
of these boards could stand to be replaced.

592
00:33:44,856 --> 00:33:46,982
Ooh!

594
00:33:51,863 --> 00:33:53,781
I just need to think light.

