00:33:53,865 --> 00:33:58,953
I'm light as a feather.

596
00:34:05,085 --> 00:34:07,336
Heavy feather.

597
00:34:07,421 --> 00:34:09,338
Okay.

598
00:34:09,423 --> 00:34:12,591
This will just pinch a little.

599
00:34:12,676 --> 00:34:16,679
l'm lighter than a feather.
What's lighter than a feather?

600
00:34:17,806 --> 00:34:19,724
Air!

601
00:34:19,808 --> 00:34:21,726
There's nothin' lighter.

602
00:34:21,810 --> 00:34:24,895
So it stands to reason—

603
00:34:24,980 --> 00:34:28,482
that the more air I have—

604
00:34:28,567 --> 00:34:30,776
the lighter—

605
00:34:30,861 --> 00:34:32,862
I'll be.

608
00:34:54,593 --> 00:34:58,220
La-aah!

614
00:35:15,071 --> 00:35:16,739
- Aah!
- Next, please.

615
00:35:16,823 --> 00:35:19,033
All right,
that was absolutely terrifying.

616
00:35:19,117 --> 00:35:21,368
If I just pull myself up—

617
00:35:22,788 --> 00:35:26,373
Try not to panic.

620
00:35:40,722 --> 00:35:42,723
Hmm.

621
00:35:45,018 --> 00:35:48,562
Whew! That could have been a disaster.

622
00:35:52,484 --> 00:35:54,401
Wow. I feel really good right now.

623
00:35:54,486 --> 00:35:57,321
Maybe it's my new sense of purpose.

624
00:36:08,834 --> 00:36:10,501
Whoa.

627
00:36:21,221 --> 00:36:23,597
All right.

628
00:36:23,682 --> 00:36:27,101
Hey! JoJo, I need your help.
Can you help me?

629
00:36:27,185 --> 00:36:30,521
Okay. Great. Okay, first  l need you
to go to the girls' room.

630
00:36:30,605 --> 00:36:33,566
Aah! Take down Hannah's
china doll collection and then—

631
00:36:33,650 --> 00:36:36,652
Stop looking at my arm. Put away
Holly's lightbulb collection and then—

632
00:36:36,736 --> 00:36:41,448
You know what?Just take care
ofanything that might break or shatter.

633
00:36:41,533 --> 00:36:44,243
Okay. Take a good, long look.

634
00:36:44,327 --> 00:36:46,370
Got it? Thanks,JoJo.

637
00:36:51,126 --> 00:36:54,795
Oww! Oh!
Whew!

638
00:36:56,172 --> 00:36:58,549
Here. And I'll take that.

639
00:36:58,633 --> 00:37:01,218
And— Oh! Aaah!

641
00:37:06,391 --> 00:37:08,976
Hi. You're home late.

642
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:13,939
Oh. Sorry, hon. I wasjust having
some dental work done on my arm.

643
00:37:14,024 --> 00:37:16,233
So, what was the— Ned!

644
00:37:16,318 --> 00:37:19,695
What are you doing?

645
00:37:19,779 --> 00:37:21,906
W-What do you mean?

646
00:37:21,990 --> 00:37:24,950
Well, I'm no detective, Ned,
but you are hanging from the chandelier.

647
00:37:25,035 --> 00:37:27,036
I just thought it might
look better somewhere...

648
00:37:27,120 --> 00:37:30,080
it can't fall on us
and crush us in our sleep.

649
00:37:30,165 --> 00:37:33,500
What is going on?

650
00:37:35,503 --> 00:37:38,756
Hey, hon—

652
00:37:41,384 --> 00:37:45,804
did you ever get the feeling
that you were being watched?

653
00:37:45,889 --> 00:37:50,184
Um, yeah. Sure. I suppose.

654
00:37:50,268 --> 00:37:53,395
And then you get the feeling
that maybe that thing watching you...

655
00:37:53,480 --> 00:37:57,441
is, uh, a giant elephant.

656
00:37:57,525 --> 00:37:59,443
Um—

657
00:37:59,527 --> 00:38:04,573
And you know howyou get that weird feeling
that your world is actually a tiny speck...

658
00:38:04,658 --> 00:38:06,575
and that the elephant...

659
00:38:06,660 --> 00:38:08,744
that l talked about earlier...

660
00:38:08,828 --> 00:38:11,246
is carrying it around on a flower...

661
00:38:11,331 --> 00:38:14,833
and you realize that ifyou tell anybody,
they'd thinkyou were crazy.

662
00:38:14,918 --> 00:38:19,797
But you still feel a responsibility
to keep everyone safe.

663
00:38:19,881 --> 00:38:21,674
You know that feeling?

664
00:38:21,758 --> 00:38:26,303
Um, you know,
I'm gonna have to say no.

665
00:38:26,388 --> 00:38:28,722
Do you know that feeling?

666
00:38:29,766 --> 00:38:32,685
Ah!
No.

667
00:38:32,769 --> 00:38:35,312
Yawn.

668
00:38:35,397 --> 00:38:38,983
Wow, I am beat.
Time to hit the hay, I guess.

669
00:38:39,067 --> 00:38:42,903
Sweetheart, I know
you're under a lot ofstress.

670
00:38:42,988 --> 00:38:47,491
And ifyou're seeing
elephants and flowers, then fine.

671
00:38:47,575 --> 00:38:50,536
Just don't tell anyone else
that story. Okay?

672
00:38:50,620 --> 00:38:55,874
And remember,
it's not the end ofthe world.

673
00:38:55,959 --> 00:38:58,711
The end ofthe world?

674
00:38:58,795 --> 00:39:02,423
Horton to Mayor. Horton to Mayor.
Come in, Mayor. Over.

675
00:39:04,300 --> 00:39:07,302
Horton? Ohh.

676
00:39:07,387 --> 00:39:09,388
I get terrible reception here.

677
00:39:09,472 --> 00:39:12,266
How about this?
If I get up real close, can you read me?

679
00:39:16,396 --> 00:39:18,480
Yep. Roger that.

680
00:39:18,565 --> 00:39:20,983
Are we at that safe place yet?

681
00:39:21,067 --> 00:39:24,278
Almost. I'm pretty sure
the worst part's over.

682
00:39:24,362 --> 00:39:26,280
This is your elephant speaking.

683
00:39:26,364 --> 00:39:29,950
Just sit back, enjoy the ride,
and we'll have you to Mount Nool in no time.

684
00:39:30,076 --> 00:39:32,953
- No, you can't have ice cream for breakfast.
- Please!

685
00:39:33,038 --> 00:39:35,956
Who's that?
Is there someone else there?

686
00:39:36,041 --> 00:39:38,542
Well, that's my wife and kids.

687
00:39:38,626 --> 00:39:41,378
- You have a family.
- I do indeed.

688
00:39:41,463 --> 00:39:44,882
A beautiful wife, 96 daughters...

689
00:39:44,966 --> 00:39:46,592
and one son.

690
00:39:46,676 --> 00:39:48,427
Oh-ho-ho-ho. Busy guy.

691
00:39:48,511 --> 00:39:51,305
And we all share one bathroom.
You know how that is.

692
00:39:51,389 --> 00:39:54,224
Yeah. Don't I know it?

693
00:39:54,309 --> 00:39:56,226
Bathroom?

694
00:39:56,311 --> 00:39:58,395
- Ned?
- What?

695
00:39:58,480 --> 00:40:00,814
Sweetheart, you know
you're on the roof, right?

696
00:40:00,899 --> 00:40:03,817
- Please, Mom.
- What's that? No, you need to go to bed.

697
00:40:03,902 --> 00:40:07,196
Daddy's having a breakdown.
Ned, what are you up to now?

698
00:40:07,280 --> 00:40:11,241
I wasjust about to put the kids to bed
when I got offthe roof.

699
00:40:11,326 --> 00:40:14,286
And, uh, that's—
that's what happened. Right.

702
00:40:29,761 --> 00:40:31,678
- Daddy?
- Yes?

703
00:40:31,763 --> 00:40:34,681
- Can I have a glass ofwater?
- Ofcourse.

704
00:40:34,766 --> 00:40:35,766
- Me two!
- Me three!

705
00:40:35,850 --> 00:40:37,851
- Me six!
- Me seven!

706
00:40:37,936 --> 00:40:39,937
- Me 39!
- Me 28!

707
00:40:40,021 --> 00:40:41,730
Okay.

708
00:40:46,903 --> 00:40:49,446
- Hey,JoJo. Whoa.
- Huh?

709
00:40:49,531 --> 00:40:53,450
Lotta liquid. Lotta liquid.
Just the person I wanted to see.

710
00:40:53,535 --> 00:40:58,038
Yeah, I realize that we have not been
seeing eye to eye lately.

711
00:40:58,123 --> 00:41:02,126
And most of it is my fault.
That's true.

712
00:41:02,210 --> 00:41:04,128
You know what I've been
trying to do?

713
00:41:04,212 --> 00:41:07,923
I have been trying to impose
my vision ofyour future on you.

714
00:41:08,007 --> 00:41:10,509
Let me make this perfectly clear.

715
00:41:10,593 --> 00:41:15,430
JoJo, you can be
whatever kind of mayoryou want to be.

716
00:41:15,515 --> 00:41:18,851
Hands-on, strong and silent, outspoken—
it's up to you.

717
00:41:18,935 --> 00:41:22,646
Well, good.
I feel so much better.

718
00:41:22,730 --> 00:41:26,483
I am expecting big things from you,
young man. Big things!

719
00:41:26,568 --> 00:41:28,485
All right. Good night.

720
00:41:28,570 --> 00:41:30,571
Good stuff. Good talk.

721
00:41:45,003 --> 00:41:48,505
Then JoJo snuck out, feeling lonely and sad...

722
00:41:48,590 --> 00:41:51,592
and tragically misunderstood
by his dad.

723
00:42:07,275 --> 00:42:09,818
And where was he going
at such a late hour?

724
00:42:12,822 --> 00:42:15,949
Up to Who-ville's
abandoned star-studying tower...

725
00:42:17,702 --> 00:42:20,996
a place where the boy
felt contented and free...

726
00:42:21,080 --> 00:42:24,499
a place he could be
what he wanted to be.

727
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:29,296
And what was inside there,
 l'd say if I could.

728
00:42:29,380 --> 00:42:33,133
But up above,
the kangaroo was up to no good.

729
00:42:40,683 --> 00:42:42,601
Can l come out now, Mom?

730
00:42:42,685 --> 00:42:44,603
No, Rudy. Stay in your room.

731
00:42:44,687 --> 00:42:46,647
- But, Mom—
- Stay inside.

732
00:42:56,783 --> 00:42:59,660
Mr. Vladikoff?

733
00:43:11,256 --> 00:43:15,175
Eating. Go.

734
00:43:15,260 --> 00:43:18,679
Yes, I-I realize you're busy,
but I need your help.

735
00:43:18,763 --> 00:43:20,681
It's Horton.

736
00:43:20,765 --> 00:43:23,308
He's become obsessed
with a clover...

737
00:43:23,393 --> 00:43:26,603
and he actually thinks
there are little people on it.

739
00:43:29,399 --> 00:43:31,400
I want that clover destroyed.

740
00:43:31,484 --> 00:43:34,528
Sure. What a big deal this is...
foryou, bro.

741
00:43:35,905 --> 00:43:38,657
I'd do it myself, but, being a lady...

742
00:43:38,741 --> 00:43:41,994
I prefer not to get my hands dirty.

743
00:43:42,078 --> 00:43:44,579
But I hearyou have
no problem with that.

744
00:43:46,082 --> 00:43:49,209
No. No problem.

745
00:43:49,294 --> 00:43:51,211
Easy peasy.

746
00:43:51,296 --> 00:43:54,381
But I will only do this
for a price...

747
00:43:54,465 --> 00:43:58,135
in exchange
for a brand-new pair of―

748
00:43:58,219 --> 00:43:59,970
No.

749
00:44:00,054 --> 00:44:01,972
This...

750
00:44:02,056 --> 00:44:04,141
- little kangaroo.
- Mom!

751
00:44:04,225 --> 00:44:07,436
Quiet, Rudy.
Mommy's thinking it over.

752
00:44:07,520 --> 00:44:08,979
Huh.

753
00:44:09,063 --> 00:44:11,565
Well, thanks,
but on second thought...

754
00:44:11,649 --> 00:44:16,445
I think I'm going to have the Wickersham
brothers take care ofthis for me.

755
00:44:16,529 --> 00:44:19,489
Yeah, ofcourse, Wickersham.
I mean, they-they're classy operation.

756
00:44:19,574 --> 00:44:22,701
They do― Wait! No!
You can't go with Wickersham!

757
00:44:22,785 --> 00:44:26,997
No, no. No, no. The Wickershams
would be perfect for thisjob.

758
00:44:27,081 --> 00:44:30,417
But they're monkeys!
Is not scary.

759
00:44:30,501 --> 00:44:34,421
Oh, thanks anyway.
Maybe next time.

760
00:44:34,505 --> 00:44:39,384
Wait. Here's what I will do
to precious clover.

761
00:44:39,469 --> 00:44:42,387
I will take it, I will crush it...

762
00:44:42,472 --> 00:44:45,849
and I will devour it.

766
00:44:52,899 --> 00:44:57,152
Bigger than it look. One second.

767
00:44:57,236 --> 00:45:00,238
Holy moly.

768
00:45:00,323 --> 00:45:03,700
Hang on.

769
00:45:04,702 --> 00:45:06,620
Then I regurgitate it.

770
00:45:06,704 --> 00:45:10,540
Then I'm gonna devour it
second time.

771
00:45:10,625 --> 00:45:12,626
So, two times devoured.

772
00:45:12,710 --> 00:45:15,128
Sounds nice.

773
00:45:15,213 --> 00:45:17,547
But l think I'll talk
to the Wickershams.

774
00:45:17,632 --> 00:45:19,257
Wait.

775
00:45:19,342 --> 00:45:21,968
Here is best part.

776
00:45:22,053 --> 00:45:26,807
I do all— gratis.

777
00:45:26,891 --> 00:45:30,977
That's free, bro.
What do you think?

778
00:45:31,062 --> 00:45:33,105
Huh?

779
00:45:33,189 --> 00:45:35,148
Deal.

780
00:45:35,233 --> 00:45:37,150
Yes! Score!

781
00:45:37,235 --> 00:45:40,362
Thanking you.
You won't regret.

783
00:45:44,659 --> 00:45:46,952
Oop!

784
00:45:47,036 --> 00:45:49,663
Whoa! Whoo!

791
00:46:13,813 --> 00:46:15,313
Mayor!

792
00:46:16,441 --> 00:46:18,358
Mayor!

793
00:46:18,443 --> 00:46:21,403
Open up, Mr. Mayor!
Mr. Mayor!

794
00:46:23,197 --> 00:46:25,782
It's snowing!
In the summer!

797
00:46:30,538 --> 00:46:33,540
Yes. Yes, it is.

798
00:46:33,624 --> 00:46:35,542
It's a dramatic change
in the weather...

799
00:46:35,626 --> 00:46:37,627
as if we were a speck
floating through space.

800
00:46:37,712 --> 00:46:41,965
I don't know how you knew,
but s-somehow you did.

801
00:46:42,049 --> 00:46:47,429
And Who-ville is headed for disaster.

802
00:46:47,513 --> 00:46:50,182
- Oh. Horton.
- What?

803
00:46:50,266 --> 00:46:52,809
Uh, nothing. I'm on it.

804
00:46:52,894 --> 00:46:55,729
It's up to us to save
the people ofWho-ville.

805
00:46:56,856 --> 00:46:59,483
- Whoa!

806
00:46:59,567 --> 00:47:02,235
You're small, but there are
a lot ofyou. Ooh!

807
00:47:02,320 --> 00:47:04,321
That's―

808
00:47:06,365 --> 00:47:08,825
Okay. Anybody else?

809
00:47:08,910 --> 00:47:11,244
Good.

810
00:47:11,329 --> 00:47:13,830
No, no. No enjoyment. This is not fun.

811
00:47:13,915 --> 00:47:17,459
It is a sign ofdoom.

812
00:47:17,543 --> 00:47:19,419
Ah, sweetie, that's—

813
00:47:19,504 --> 00:47:22,255
No! No, no, no, no.
Danger! Danger!

814
00:47:22,340 --> 00:47:24,049
- Whee!
- Whoa!

815
00:47:24,133 --> 00:47:26,885
Stop having fun immediately!

816
00:47:26,969 --> 00:47:28,428
This is dangerous.

817
00:47:28,513 --> 00:47:32,015
Okay.

818
00:47:32,099 --> 00:47:34,059
Snowbank!

820
00:47:39,649 --> 00:47:42,984
- Horton!
- Huh? What?

822
00:47:50,117 --> 00:47:52,035
Hey there.

823
00:47:52,119 --> 00:47:53,912
We're in big trouble down here.

824
00:47:53,996 --> 00:47:56,831
It's happening. It's snowing
in the middle ofsummer.

825
00:47:56,916 --> 00:47:59,125
- It's the end ofthe world!
- Whee!

826
00:48:01,712 --> 00:48:04,422
Hold on, Mayor.
I think I know what your problem is.

828
00:48:10,721 --> 00:48:13,431
Aw!

830
00:48:16,269 --> 00:48:18,228
There. That better?

832
00:48:20,606 --> 00:48:22,524
That seems to have worked.

833
00:48:22,608 --> 00:48:25,193
Do I smell peanuts?

834
00:48:25,278 --> 00:48:27,862
Yeah. They're my favorite snack.

835
00:48:27,947 --> 00:48:30,615
But they tend to linger.

836
00:48:30,700 --> 00:48:33,451
Bleh!

837
00:48:33,536 --> 00:48:36,162
Oh!
Finwick, no.

838
00:48:36,330 --> 00:48:39,207
Uh-oh. Hang on, Mr. Mayor.

839
00:48:39,292 --> 00:48:43,378
I may have to put up a fight.
A frightened elephant can be very dangerous!

840
00:48:43,462 --> 00:48:47,007
All right! You've called down
the thunder, buddy!

841
00:48:47,091 --> 00:48:51,344
You hungry for trouble?
I'm an all-you-can-eat salad bar. Take a bite!

842
00:48:53,347 --> 00:48:55,765
I hate running.

843
00:48:55,850 --> 00:48:57,767
Morton?

844
00:48:57,852 --> 00:48:59,978
Don't do that.

845
00:49:00,062 --> 00:49:02,314
Horton!

846
00:49:02,398 --> 00:49:05,025
Horton— D'oh!
There you are.

847
00:49:05,109 --> 00:49:07,902
We got trouble. Wait.
Stay, wait. Did you hear that?

848
00:49:07,987 --> 00:49:09,946
No, I'm here.
Okay, listen. No. Go.

849
00:49:10,031 --> 00:49:12,907
Kangaroo has gone nuts, bananas.

850
00:49:12,992 --> 00:49:15,619
She's telling everyone that you
should be kicked out of Nool.

851
00:49:15,703 --> 00:49:18,580
She said that?
I thought we were friends.

852
00:49:18,664 --> 00:49:21,541
- Word is she's gone to Vlad.
- Vlad?

853
00:49:21,626 --> 00:49:24,294
Vlad. I know two Vlads.

854
00:49:24,378 --> 00:49:28,173
Is it the bad Vlad
or the bunny Vlad that makes the cookies?

855
00:49:28,257 --> 00:49:31,968
Yeah, Horton, she's sending you
a bunny with cookies.

856
00:49:32,053 --> 00:49:34,638
I think we can assume
it's the bad Vlad.

857
00:49:34,722 --> 00:49:36,348
Yeah, that's a good call.

858
00:49:36,432 --> 00:49:41,019
So unless you're cool
with giant, razor-sharp claws...

859
00:49:41,103 --> 00:49:43,647
ripping the flesh offyour body...

860
00:49:43,731 --> 00:49:45,440
I'd get rid ofthe clover.

