00:49:45,524 --> 00:49:48,360
I can't. I promised the mayor.

862
00:49:48,444 --> 00:49:51,529
I meant what  l said,
and I said what I meant.

863
00:49:51,614 --> 00:49:53,823
And an elephant's faithful 1 00%.

864
00:49:53,908 --> 00:49:56,868
Please, for me,just this once...

865
00:49:56,952 --> 00:49:59,621
be faithful 99% ofthe time.

866
00:49:59,705 --> 00:50:01,790
I've never gotten 99% on anything.

867
00:50:01,874 --> 00:50:03,792
And l think I'm awesome.
So come on.

868
00:50:03,876 --> 00:50:08,254
I meant what I said,
and I said what I meant.

869
00:50:08,339 --> 00:50:10,715
I'm not gonna say it.

870
00:50:10,800 --> 00:50:12,801
You can do that all day.
It's not happening.

871
00:50:14,136 --> 00:50:16,513
- An elephant's faithful 1 00%.
- That's right.

872
00:50:16,597 --> 00:50:20,475
That's my code, my motto.
But thanks for the warning.

873
00:50:20,559 --> 00:50:22,852
"Motto." Okay.

874
00:50:22,937 --> 00:50:24,896
But watch the skies.

875
00:50:24,980 --> 00:50:29,109
Keep watching the skies!

876
00:50:32,738 --> 00:50:36,199
Mayor! You need to get
everyone underground now!

877
00:50:36,283 --> 00:50:38,618
- Two, three, four.
- I don't want to sound the alarm.

878
00:50:38,703 --> 00:50:40,995
But there's a good possibility...

879
00:50:41,080 --> 00:50:43,998
- we may be attacked by a giant, carnivorous bird.
- What?

880
00:50:44,083 --> 00:50:47,460
There's a small chance it could be a bunny
with cookies, but I wouldn't count on it.

881
00:50:48,671 --> 00:50:51,256
Oh, they are formidable. Whoop.

882
00:50:51,340 --> 00:50:53,425
Mayor? Are you there?

883
00:50:53,509 --> 00:50:55,427
Yeah. No, that's a great idea.

884
00:50:55,511 --> 00:50:58,388
It'sjust—
In order to get everyone mobilized...

885
00:50:58,472 --> 00:51:01,015
I'd need the okay
ofthe city council.

886
00:51:01,100 --> 00:51:03,768
And they never listen to me.

887
00:51:03,853 --> 00:51:06,646
I've been called a boob—
several times.

888
00:51:06,731 --> 00:51:07,647
I can't do it.

889
00:51:07,815 --> 00:51:10,567
You have to talk to them, Mayor.
Okay, listen.

891
00:51:12,820 --> 00:51:15,405
Bad Vlad! Bad Vlad!

892
00:51:15,489 --> 00:51:18,366
Ooh! Bad Vlad!

895
00:51:24,582 --> 00:51:27,417
That is definitely not a bunny.

896
00:51:33,257 --> 00:51:36,593
Lost him.

897
00:51:36,677 --> 00:51:39,429
Meant to lose him, and I lost him.
Heh. Yeah.

900
00:51:44,977 --> 00:51:46,561
This tree for real?
Come on.

901
00:51:46,645 --> 00:51:49,606
Hang on, Who-ville!
This is gonna get rough!

902
00:51:49,690 --> 00:51:53,109
Oh!

905
00:52:00,868 --> 00:52:02,869
Now you're going to get it!

906
00:52:03,871 --> 00:52:05,789
Get ready for the best!

908
00:52:08,626 --> 00:52:10,543
Leave me alone!

909
00:52:11,962 --> 00:52:13,254
Hort― Ow!

910
00:52:14,298 --> 00:52:17,217
Horton!

913
00:52:23,641 --> 00:52:27,769
Whew!

914
00:52:27,853 --> 00:52:30,313
I just know he's gonna
jump out somewhere.

915
00:52:30,397 --> 00:52:32,857
- Hello.

919
00:52:43,118 --> 00:52:45,495
Ooph!

922
00:52:51,961 --> 00:52:54,212
"Chessmate."

923
00:52:54,296 --> 00:52:56,798
Now it's time for me
to take clover...

924
00:52:56,882 --> 00:52:58,842
and crush all
the little people on it.

925
00:52:58,926 --> 00:53:02,095
Sorry, this is where we get off.

927
00:53:05,808 --> 00:53:09,018
Right in the beak!

928
00:53:09,103 --> 00:53:11,396
Cool line.

929
00:53:11,480 --> 00:53:13,481
Usually I can't think
ofthose things till later.

930
00:53:13,607 --> 00:53:15,942
- Mayor?
- Ah, Horton.

931
00:53:16,026 --> 00:53:19,404
- Are you okay?
- Um—

933
00:53:21,991 --> 00:53:25,368
Well, more or less.

934
00:53:25,452 --> 00:53:28,788
- What happened? The bird?
- Yeah, it attacked me.

935
00:53:28,873 --> 00:53:31,040
Mayor, your people are in danger.

936
00:53:31,125 --> 00:53:34,335
Huh? You know what?
I'm gonna do it.

937
00:53:34,420 --> 00:53:37,463
I am going to go out there
and tell them what is going on.

938
00:53:37,548 --> 00:53:39,924
Perfect. Now, quick, get going.

940
00:53:45,139 --> 00:53:48,516
Hey, Mr. Mayor! Something's wrong!

941
00:53:48,601 --> 00:53:50,810
My basement is in the attic!

942
00:53:50,895 --> 00:53:53,187
- The science museum is history!
- The Lost and Found is missing!

943
00:53:53,272 --> 00:53:55,440
What's going on, Mr. Mayor?

944
00:53:55,524 --> 00:53:57,984
I'm declaring a state ofemergency!

945
00:53:58,068 --> 00:54:00,904
 Don't worry! Don't worry!

946
00:54:00,988 --> 00:54:03,656
The mayor is just being a moron.

947
00:54:03,741 --> 00:54:06,910
No, wait! Who-ville is in terrible danger.

948
00:54:06,994 --> 00:54:11,623
Everyone needs to get down
to the underground storage area immediately!

949
00:54:11,707 --> 00:54:16,419
Fine! Fine.
Let's do this democratically.

950
00:54:16,503 --> 00:54:21,883
Who wants thejoy and glory
and festivity ofthe Who-centennial...

951
00:54:21,967 --> 00:54:23,927
to proceed as planned?

953
00:54:26,472 --> 00:54:30,433
- And who, like the mayor—
- Uh—

954
00:54:30,517 --> 00:54:33,478
thinks it would be better
to spend the Who-centennial...

955
00:54:33,562 --> 00:54:36,856
in an underground storage area?

956
00:54:37,900 --> 00:54:39,609
Yeah!

957
00:54:39,693 --> 00:54:43,488
Wait! You've got to listen to me!

958
00:54:43,572 --> 00:54:46,449
Our whole world could explode!

960
00:54:50,704 --> 00:54:52,956
Much more quickly!

961
00:54:53,040 --> 00:54:54,958
And ourworld wouldn't
make that noise.

962
00:54:55,042 --> 00:55:00,213
The people have spoken, Mr. Mayor.

963
00:55:00,297 --> 00:55:04,300
You're finished.
No one believes you.

964
00:55:04,385 --> 00:55:07,637
No one supports you.

965
00:55:07,721 --> 00:55:10,515
Horton believes me.

966
00:55:10,599 --> 00:55:13,059
Horton?

967
00:55:13,143 --> 00:55:15,061
Who's Horton?

968
00:55:15,145 --> 00:55:20,566
Horton is a giant elephant in the sky!

969
00:55:20,651 --> 00:55:23,069
- Huh?
- Don't bother looking. He's invisible.

970
00:55:23,153 --> 00:55:26,864
And he's the one
risking his life to get Who-ville—

971
00:55:26,949 --> 00:55:31,786
which, by the way,
is a speck on a clover― to safety!

975
00:55:43,590 --> 00:55:47,760
l can prove it.
Horton's voice comes out ofthis horn.

976
00:55:50,014 --> 00:55:51,806
He's lost his mind.

977
00:55:51,890 --> 00:55:53,599
Horton!

978
00:55:53,684 --> 00:55:57,687
I have all the Whos
gathered in Town Square.

979
00:55:57,771 --> 00:56:00,064
Let them knowyou're there!

980
00:56:00,149 --> 00:56:02,692
Gee.

981
00:56:02,776 --> 00:56:05,111
This is kind ofa high-pressure
situation then.

982
00:56:05,195 --> 00:56:07,363
l don't hear anything.

983
00:56:07,448 --> 00:56:10,241
Wow. I am really drawing a blank here.

984
00:56:10,325 --> 00:56:12,243
I know!

986
00:56:15,330 --> 00:56:17,582
Horton.

987
00:56:17,666 --> 00:56:19,834
Horton, we're waiting.

988
00:56:19,918 --> 00:56:22,795
Time to show everyone
that you exist...

989
00:56:22,880 --> 00:56:27,800
and, by extension,
what a non-boob I am.

992
00:56:33,974 --> 00:56:37,351
Wait! Everyone, look at the wind.

993
00:56:37,436 --> 00:56:39,771
What do you think that that means?

994
00:56:41,398 --> 00:56:43,316
It means—

995
00:56:43,400 --> 00:56:45,943
It means, obviously―

996
00:56:46,028 --> 00:56:50,198
Let the kite-flying race begin!

998
00:57:07,299 --> 00:57:10,301
What a burn on you, Horton!

1005
00:58:05,607 --> 00:58:08,109
Ooh! Brain freeze!

1008
00:58:14,449 --> 00:58:17,743
Give me back...

1009
00:58:17,828 --> 00:58:19,579
- my speck!
- Huh?

1010
00:58:19,663 --> 00:58:22,248
Not this time, guy.

1012
00:58:27,462 --> 00:58:29,839
I am so sorry that I let you down.

1013
00:58:29,923 --> 00:58:34,135
But this― This is bigger than me.

1014
00:58:34,219 --> 00:58:37,013
Get the family together
and get somewhere safe!

1015
00:58:37,097 --> 00:58:40,683
I will! I believe you.

1017
00:58:46,273 --> 00:58:49,108
I've got you now, elephant.

1018
00:58:49,193 --> 00:58:52,320
No! No! No!

1020
00:59:03,999 --> 00:59:05,124
Oh, no.

1021
00:59:07,711 --> 00:59:09,128
Oh!

1023
00:59:12,090 --> 00:59:14,800
Yeah!

1026
00:59:33,153 --> 00:59:35,071
Mayor?

1027
00:59:35,155 --> 00:59:38,783
Anybody there? Hello?

1028
00:59:40,077 --> 00:59:41,953
Anyone?

1029
00:59:42,037 --> 00:59:45,081
But clover by clover by clover, he found...

1030
00:59:45,165 --> 00:59:48,876
that the one that he sought for
was just not around.

1031
00:59:48,961 --> 00:59:50,962
Mayor?

1032
00:59:53,090 --> 00:59:54,674
Hello?

1033
00:59:54,758 --> 00:59:57,760
And by noon,
poor Horton, more dead than alive...

1034
00:59:57,844 --> 01:00:02,556
had picked, searched and piled up
nine thousand and five.

1035
01:00:02,641 --> 01:00:05,101
Hello?

1036
01:00:05,185 --> 01:00:08,312
Sorry to botheryou, nobody.

1037
01:00:11,692 --> 01:00:15,027
Knock, knock.

1038
01:00:15,112 --> 01:00:18,614
This is where you'd say,
"Whos there?"

1039
01:00:18,699 --> 01:00:22,827
If there were any Whos there.

1040
01:00:22,911 --> 01:00:26,622
Get it? "Whos there?"

1042
01:00:30,210 --> 01:00:33,671
All day he looked, looked on and on...

1043
01:00:34,715 --> 01:00:37,341
until his hope was almost gone.

1044
01:00:37,426 --> 01:00:39,343
No, no.

1045
01:00:39,428 --> 01:00:41,429
No! Please, no!

1046
01:00:41,513 --> 01:00:43,556
Oh! This isn't fair!

1047
01:00:47,561 --> 01:00:49,687
But wait!

1048
01:00:49,771 --> 01:00:53,733
Could this one be the one?
Was all his searching finally done?

1049
01:00:53,817 --> 01:00:56,652
Ah, yes.
For this was the hour.

1050
01:00:56,737 --> 01:01:00,489
Horton had found them
on the three-millionth flower.

1051
01:01:00,574 --> 01:01:04,910
Mayor! Mayor! I found you!

1052
01:01:06,705 --> 01:01:08,539
Mayor?

1053
01:01:08,623 --> 01:01:10,541
Are you there?

1054
01:01:10,625 --> 01:01:12,710
Mayor?

1056
01:01:15,589 --> 01:01:17,590
Mayor.

1057
01:01:24,139 --> 01:01:26,474
Mayor, are you there?

1058
01:01:29,186 --> 01:01:31,187
Mayor.

1059
01:01:35,942 --> 01:01:42,239
Mayor?

1060
01:01:43,658 --> 01:01:46,827
Mayor!

1062
01:01:52,959 --> 01:01:58,047
Uh, no. This is Floyd.

1063
01:01:58,131 --> 01:02:01,634
Can I take a message?

1064
01:02:04,137 --> 01:02:07,348
Mayor! You're okay!

1066
01:02:09,226 --> 01:02:11,894
Horton! Horton!
Stop! Stop it!

1068
01:02:16,483 --> 01:02:19,276
Sorry. It must've been rough down there.

1069
01:02:19,361 --> 01:02:23,072
l can't believe I found you.
You really had me worried.

1070
01:02:23,156 --> 01:02:26,659
Say! The mayor was right!

1071
01:02:26,743 --> 01:02:28,661
Daddy! Daddy! Daddy!

1072
01:02:28,745 --> 01:02:30,663
Oh! Okay, I'm all right.

1073
01:02:30,747 --> 01:02:32,832
- Toof!
- And so are you.

1074
01:02:36,378 --> 01:02:39,797
Citizens ofWho-ville!

1075
01:02:41,883 --> 01:02:46,387
I'd like you to meet
our friend Horton.

1077
01:02:50,475 --> 01:02:54,562
He's going to help us.

1078
01:02:54,646 --> 01:02:56,564
l've got this.

1079
01:02:56,648 --> 01:02:59,150
- This is the chairman.
- Idiot!

1080
01:02:59,234 --> 01:03:01,694
You're finished in this town.
Is that understood?

1081
01:03:01,778 --> 01:03:04,071
Finished! You boob!

1082
01:03:04,156 --> 01:03:08,159
No, I'm justjoking.

1083
01:03:08,243 --> 01:03:09,702
Oh.

1085
01:03:11,288 --> 01:03:12,955
Good one.

1086
01:03:13,039 --> 01:03:15,624
Horton, this is my wife, Sally.

1087
01:03:15,709 --> 01:03:18,627
You exist!
This means my husband isn't crazy.

1088
01:03:18,712 --> 01:03:20,963
Hooray!

1089
01:03:21,047 --> 01:03:23,215
And a few of my daughters:

1090
01:03:23,300 --> 01:03:26,427
- Haley, Holly, Hooly, Hilda and Hedy.
- Hi!

1091
01:03:26,511 --> 01:03:30,139
And here is Miss Yelp, my loyal assistant.

1092
01:03:30,223 --> 01:03:33,392
- And here's Dr. Larue.
- You saved us!

1093
01:03:33,477 --> 01:03:37,521
And Burt from Accounting.
And Mrs. McGillicuddy and Mr. Farfoogan.

1094
01:03:37,606 --> 01:03:39,356
- From the Clugan Farfoogans.
- Oi! Oi! Oi!

1095
01:03:39,441 --> 01:03:41,192
And the old man in the bathtub.

1096
01:03:41,276 --> 01:03:44,612
Let's not overwhelm the poor fella.
He's never gonna remember all these names.

1097
01:03:44,696 --> 01:03:47,948
Well, I'll try my best...

1098
01:03:48,033 --> 01:03:50,910
Sally, Chairman...

1099
01:03:50,994 --> 01:03:53,454
Haley, Hooly, Holly, Hilda, Hedy.
Miss Yelp.

1100
01:03:53,538 --> 01:03:55,331
Dr. Larue, Burt from Accounting,
Mrs. McGillicuddy...

1101
01:03:55,415 --> 01:03:57,208
Mr. Farfoogan
ofthe Clugan Farfoogans.

1102
01:03:57,292 --> 01:04:00,336
And wasn't there an old guy
in a shower?

1103
01:04:00,420 --> 01:04:02,671
- Mmm, bathtub.
- Ooh! Yeah.

1104
01:04:02,756 --> 01:04:05,382
We're all here, Horton.

1105
01:04:05,467 --> 01:04:09,303
And we all believe in you.

1106
01:04:09,387 --> 01:04:11,305
Wow. That's awesome.

1107
01:04:11,389 --> 01:04:14,350
And it's a responsibility
l do not take lightly.

1108
01:04:14,434 --> 01:04:18,479
l promise you a future
that is safe, sound and stable.

1109
01:04:18,563 --> 01:04:23,817
We will create a world where every Who
is endowed with three inalienable rights...

1110
01:04:23,902 --> 01:04:25,819
to be determined at a later date.

1111
01:04:25,946 --> 01:04:29,782
And, uh, we will, uh,
put a speck on Mount Nool...

1112
01:04:29,866 --> 01:04:32,117
before the end ofthis, uh, decade.

1113
01:04:36,414 --> 01:04:38,040
Oh!

1114
01:04:38,124 --> 01:04:40,751
This-This elephant is crazy!

1115
01:04:40,835 --> 01:04:43,295
Oh, my goodness.
I gotta tell everybody.

1116
01:04:43,380 --> 01:04:46,257
I need to get to the kangaroo. Whoo!

1117
01:04:46,341 --> 01:04:48,467
Wait till they find out about― Oh!

1118
01:04:48,552 --> 01:04:52,263
Oh! You should have been seeing me.
l really let elephant have it.

1119
01:04:52,347 --> 01:04:54,265
I chase him. I torment him.

1120
01:04:54,349 --> 01:04:56,725
I break him into million
little elephant pieces.

1121
01:04:56,810 --> 01:04:59,270
It was thing of beauty. Really.

1122
01:04:59,354 --> 01:05:01,730
My best work. Classic Vlad.

1123
01:05:01,815 --> 01:05:04,567
- And the clover?
- Clover is finished.

1124
01:05:04,651 --> 01:05:06,986
No way in million years
Horton find it.

1125
01:05:07,070 --> 01:05:10,614
Read my beak.
Clover is gone forever.

1128
01:05:16,413 --> 01:05:18,914
I just saw Horton,
and he is still talkin' to that clover!

1130
01:05:21,251 --> 01:05:25,254
ldiot!

1131
01:05:25,338 --> 01:05:27,965
Whoa. Come on.
I'm your bro.

1132
01:05:28,049 --> 01:05:30,634
It's me you are talking to.
We have history.

1133
01:05:30,719 --> 01:05:33,804
Come on. Let's not forget—
I did this for free.

1134
01:05:34,848 --> 01:05:38,183
What is happening
to theJungle of Nool?

1135
01:05:38,268 --> 01:05:41,687
There once was a time
when people were people...

1136
01:05:41,771 --> 01:05:44,732
- and specks were specks.
- Mm-hmm.

1137
01:05:44,816 --> 01:05:48,485
Well, I say,
ifyou can't see it, hear it or feel it...

1138
01:05:48,570 --> 01:05:50,529
it doesn't exist!

1139
01:05:51,781 --> 01:05:54,366
Our way of life is under attack.

1140
01:05:54,451 --> 01:05:57,244
And who's leading that attack? Horton!

1141
01:05:57,329 --> 01:05:58,787
Whoa!

1142
01:05:58,872 --> 01:06:00,623
Whoa! Whoa!

1143
01:06:00,707 --> 01:06:03,167
Wait a minute.
This is Horton we're talking about.

1144
01:06:03,251 --> 01:06:06,086
You all know him.
He wouldn't hurt a fly―

1145
01:06:06,171 --> 01:06:09,715
except for that fly city he sat on,
but he didn't do that on purpose.

1146
01:06:09,799 --> 01:06:11,634
Shut up, mouse.

1147
01:06:11,718 --> 01:06:14,553
Yeah. That's weird.

1148
01:06:14,638 --> 01:06:17,014
My brownies are burning.
I gotta go.

1149
01:06:18,224 --> 01:06:20,392
Are we going to let
troublemakers like Horton...

1150
01:06:20,477 --> 01:06:23,437
poison the minds ofour children?

1151
01:06:23,521 --> 01:06:25,564
Not the children!

1152
01:06:25,649 --> 01:06:30,444
When Horton tells the children
about worlds beyond thejungle...

1153
01:06:30,528 --> 01:06:33,072
he makes them question authority―

1154
01:06:33,156 --> 01:06:37,284
which leads to defiance,
which leads to anarchy!

1155
01:06:37,369 --> 01:06:40,037
Yeah! Horton must pay!

1156
01:06:40,121 --> 01:06:43,624
- It's that speck!
- We have to do something!

1157
01:06:43,708 --> 01:06:46,377
- For the children!
- For the children!

1158
01:06:46,461 --> 01:06:51,131
Are we going to let him
get away with this?

1159
01:06:51,216 --> 01:06:53,676
No!

1160
01:06:53,760 --> 01:06:55,844
Let's get him!

1164
01:07:14,447 --> 01:07:16,407
Hmm?

1165
01:07:16,491 --> 01:07:19,368
Morton?

1166
01:07:19,452 --> 01:07:22,413
l told you— 100%!

1167
01:07:22,497 --> 01:07:24,081
Horton!

1168
01:07:24,165 --> 01:07:26,959
Morton, pick up your feet. Geez!

1169
01:07:27,043 --> 01:07:29,044
It's not me!

1170
01:07:30,171 --> 01:07:33,340
Oh. I see. It's an angry mob.

1171
01:07:33,425 --> 01:07:36,593
Sorry, Morton. I thought it was you
that was making all the―

1172
01:07:36,678 --> 01:07:39,430
But it's― Oh, darn.

1173
01:07:39,514 --> 01:07:41,181
Everybody! Come on!

1174
01:07:41,266 --> 01:07:43,434
Run, Horton!

1175
01:07:43,518 --> 01:07:45,978
- There he is!
- Get the speck!

1176
01:07:46,062 --> 01:07:47,813
Let's rope him!

1177
01:07:47,897 --> 01:07:50,524
Let's cage him!

1178
01:07:50,608 --> 01:07:52,443
No!

1180
01:07:57,073 --> 01:07:59,992
Stop!

1181
01:08:00,076 --> 01:08:04,121
Hey, fellas. Good to see ya— all at once.

1182
01:08:04,205 --> 01:08:05,956
You look really great as a horde.

1183
01:08:06,040 --> 01:08:07,958
Horton, Horton, Horton.

1184
01:08:08,042 --> 01:08:11,879
Look at the mess
you've created foryourself.

1185
01:08:11,963 --> 01:08:15,507
All this hullabaloo
over a silly little flower.

1186
01:08:15,592 --> 01:08:17,760
It's a speck.

1187
01:08:17,844 --> 01:08:20,888
Right. I mean, it's silly, really...

1188
01:08:20,972 --> 01:08:24,516
all this talk of roping you
and caging you, and, well...

1189
01:08:24,601 --> 01:08:27,352
we don't need to go
into the details.

1190
01:08:27,437 --> 01:08:31,982
The point is, this angry mob,
all-all the trouble you're in—

1191
01:08:32,066 --> 01:08:34,651
it can all go away.

1192
01:08:34,736 --> 01:08:37,946
Really?

1193
01:08:38,031 --> 01:08:40,282
Of course.

1194
01:08:40,366 --> 01:08:43,452
All you have to do
is admit to everyone...

1195
01:08:43,536 --> 01:08:47,247
that there are no little people
living on that speck...

1196
01:08:47,332 --> 01:08:51,877
that you were wrong and I was right.

1197
01:08:51,961 --> 01:08:56,882
You do that, and things can go
right back to the way they were.

1198
01:08:56,966 --> 01:09:00,552
But ifyou don't...

1199
01:09:00,637 --> 01:09:04,139
you're going to have
to pay the price.

1202
01:09:10,188 --> 01:09:13,607
Heh. So l just have
to say it isn't true.

1203
01:09:15,109 --> 01:09:17,110
Hmm.

1204
01:09:19,614 --> 01:09:22,199
Go ahead— rope me, cage me.

1205
01:09:22,283 --> 01:09:24,201
Do whateveryou want.

1206
01:09:24,285 --> 01:09:26,203
But there are people
on this speck...

1207
01:09:26,287 --> 01:09:30,833
and they have a mayor who has 96 daughters
and one son named JoJo...

1208
01:09:30,917 --> 01:09:33,877
who all share a bathroom,
whatever that is.

1210
01:09:35,713 --> 01:09:38,799
And even though
you can't hear or see them at all...

1211
01:09:38,883 --> 01:09:42,803
a person's a person,
no matter how small.

1212
01:09:42,887 --> 01:09:46,139
Huh? Hmm?

1213
01:09:49,269 --> 01:09:52,521
That was beautiful, Horton.

1214
01:09:52,605 --> 01:09:54,815
Rope him! Cage him!

1215
01:09:54,899 --> 01:09:58,902
Burn that speck
in a pot of boiling Beezlenut oil!

1216
01:09:58,987 --> 01:10:00,654
Hmm.

1218
01:10:02,574 --> 01:10:04,867
They don't believe we're here.

1219
01:10:04,951 --> 01:10:07,411
We've got to make some noise!

1220
01:10:07,495 --> 01:10:09,746
We are here! We are here!
We are here!

1221
01:10:09,831 --> 01:10:11,915
We are here. We are here. We are here.

1222
01:10:12,000 --> 01:10:14,251
- We are here! We are here!
- Come on!

1223
01:10:14,335 --> 01:10:16,128
We are here! We are here!

1224
01:10:16,212 --> 01:10:18,463
- Everybody!
- We are here! We are here!

1225
01:10:18,548 --> 01:10:20,799
We are here! We are here!
We are here!

1229
01:10:29,309 --> 01:10:32,936
This will teach you not to make up stories
about people on specks!

1230
01:10:33,021 --> 01:10:35,480
Listen. There they are!

1231
01:10:39,527 --> 01:10:41,653
- Rope him!
- Cage him!

1232
01:10:41,738 --> 01:10:43,864
It's not working.

1233
01:10:43,948 --> 01:10:45,741
I can hearyou, but their ears
aren't strong enough.

1234
01:10:45,825 --> 01:10:48,160
We need to be louder!

1235
01:10:48,244 --> 01:10:51,622
Get every Who to make noise!
Everyone!

1236
01:10:51,706 --> 01:10:54,750
We are here!
We are here! We are here! We are here!

1237
01:10:54,834 --> 01:10:57,461
JoJo, where are you going?

1238
01:10:57,545 --> 01:11:00,797
We need every voice! JoJo!

1239
01:11:03,968 --> 01:11:06,011
You need to make some noise
down there...

1240
01:11:06,095 --> 01:11:08,263
or we'll all be destroyed!

1241
01:11:08,348 --> 01:11:11,850
The mayor grabbed a tom-tom
and started to smack it.

1243
01:11:13,811 --> 01:11:17,105
And all over Who-ville,
they whooped up a racket.

1245
01:11:19,651 --> 01:11:22,277
They rattled tin kettles.
They beat on brass pans.

1246
01:11:22,362 --> 01:11:24,488
On garbage pail tops
and old cranberry cans.

1247
01:11:24,572 --> 01:11:27,783
They blew on bazookas
and blasted great toots.

1248
01:11:27,867 --> 01:11:30,369
On clarinets, oom-pahs
and boom-pahs and flutes.

1251
01:11:32,580 --> 01:11:34,790
There!

1252
01:11:34,874 --> 01:11:36,750
We are here!
We are here!

1253
01:11:36,834 --> 01:11:38,794
Can they hear us now?

1254
01:11:38,878 --> 01:11:40,963
Listen, please!

1255
01:11:41,047 --> 01:11:43,048
It's the most beautiful thing ever.

1256
01:11:43,132 --> 01:11:45,050
- I don't hear nothin'!

1257
01:11:45,134 --> 01:11:48,220
I don't think so.
But keep trying!

1258
01:11:48,304 --> 01:11:51,473
I'll never give in!

1260
01:11:54,936 --> 01:11:59,815
Are you sure that every Who
down in Who-ville is trying?

1261
01:11:59,899 --> 01:12:04,861
♪ We are here, we are here ♪

1262
01:12:06,739 --> 01:12:07,906
We are here! We are here!

1263
01:12:07,991 --> 01:12:11,743
- Where's JoJo?
- Probably at the old observatory.

1264
01:12:11,828 --> 01:12:15,330
♪ We are here
We are here ♪

1268
01:12:24,382 --> 01:12:27,050
Oh! Oh! Hey!
There's a limit!

1272
01:12:34,225 --> 01:12:38,645
That's not supposed to stretch that far!
Ow! Ow! Ow!

1273
01:12:38,730 --> 01:12:41,398
Oh.

1275
01:12:46,988 --> 01:12:50,282
JoJo. You built this?

1282
01:13:26,110 --> 01:13:28,153
Whoa-hoo-hoo!

1283
01:13:28,237 --> 01:13:30,322
Ooh!

1285
01:13:41,167 --> 01:13:47,214
We are here!
We are here!

1287
01:13:49,383 --> 01:13:52,469
We are here! We are here!
We are here! We are here!

1291
01:14:00,103 --> 01:14:01,812
You're making a mistake!

1293
01:14:04,607 --> 01:14:06,525
- But, Mom!
- This doesn't concern you, sweetie.

1294
01:14:06,609 --> 01:14:08,360
Back in your pouch!

1296
01:14:11,322 --> 01:14:13,281
♪ We are here
We are here ♪

1297
01:14:13,366 --> 01:14:15,325
Everybody! Don't stop!

1298
01:14:17,245 --> 01:14:20,831
Keep going!
This is gonna do it!

1299
01:14:20,915 --> 01:14:24,000
We are here! We are here!

1300
01:14:25,128 --> 01:14:27,712
- Can they hear?
- No!

1302
01:14:30,842 --> 01:14:32,801
We are here. We are here.

1303
01:14:32,885 --> 01:14:36,304
We are here. We are here.
We are here.

1304
01:14:36,389 --> 01:14:40,058
No matterwhat happens,
I couldn't ask for a better son.

1305
01:14:43,271 --> 01:14:45,897
Hey.JoJo?

1306
01:14:45,982 --> 01:14:49,526
- Come on! Keep going!
- We are here!

1308
01:14:52,697 --> 01:14:54,698
No!

1310
01:14:59,036 --> 01:15:01,454
We are here! We are here!

1311
01:15:01,539 --> 01:15:03,540
We are here!
We are here!

1312
01:15:06,919 --> 01:15:08,128
No!

1313
01:15:09,922 --> 01:15:12,966
We are here! We are here!
We are here!

1315
01:15:14,594 --> 01:15:17,888
Yopp!

1316
01:15:17,972 --> 01:15:21,600
We are here!
We are here!

1318
01:15:25,438 --> 01:15:28,440
We are here!
We are here!

1319
01:15:28,608 --> 01:15:31,401
I hear it! I hear it!

1320
01:15:31,485 --> 01:15:33,028
They are there!

1321
01:15:33,112 --> 01:15:34,738
And that "yopp"...

1322
01:15:34,822 --> 01:15:37,365
that one small extra "yopp"
put it over...

1323
01:15:37,450 --> 01:15:40,410
and all the Who noises
burst out ofthe clover.

1324
01:15:40,494 --> 01:15:42,245
- I hear it!
- Me too!
- So do I!

1325
01:15:42,330 --> 01:15:44,372
We are here!
We are here!

1326
01:15:44,457 --> 01:15:47,334
Rudy, give me that.
Come. Ru—

1327
01:15:49,587 --> 01:15:53,340
Rudy, get back in the pouch. Now.

1328
01:15:55,384 --> 01:15:57,135
No, Mom.

1329
01:15:58,304 --> 01:16:00,764
Wha— Wickershams, get that clover!

1330
01:16:03,476 --> 01:16:07,229
Well, a-anybody, take it from him.

1331
01:16:07,313 --> 01:16:09,814
- Hmm?
- Oh!

1332
01:16:18,491 --> 01:16:21,743
You did it, Mayor. You did it.

1333
01:16:21,827 --> 01:16:23,828
We did it!

1335
01:16:27,250 --> 01:16:30,710
- Yeah!
- Whoo!

1336
01:16:33,381 --> 01:16:35,924
Well done, Son.

1337
01:16:36,008 --> 01:16:38,134
All right, Mayor!

1338
01:16:38,219 --> 01:16:41,346
Dad! You're one ofthe greats.

1340
01:16:45,101 --> 01:16:48,144
Whoa! Easy, everyone. Easy!

1341
01:16:49,522 --> 01:16:52,148
Oh, hi, Vlad.

1343
01:16:54,986 --> 01:16:57,237
Well, I shouldn't, but—

1346
01:17:24,557 --> 01:17:28,643
Oh, man, that is nice touch.

1347
01:17:28,728 --> 01:17:31,146
I am a mess with this, right?
Emotional!

1348
01:17:31,230 --> 01:17:33,815
Here come the waterslide!

1349
01:17:33,899 --> 01:17:37,193
There's so many people to thank―

1350
01:17:37,278 --> 01:17:39,195
the good people of Nool...

1351
01:17:39,280 --> 01:17:42,574
- who put me in a cage and poked me with sticks.
- That was me!

1352
01:17:42,658 --> 01:17:46,995
My buddy Morton, for being the only one
who stood by me. Well, not right by me.

1353
01:17:47,079 --> 01:17:50,623
He hid in the bushes,
sending me good thoughts. He's small.

1354
01:17:50,708 --> 01:17:53,251
Dude, you are a warrior poet.

1355
01:17:53,419 --> 01:17:56,629
And most ofall,
I'd like to thank the mayor ofWho-ville...

1356
01:17:56,714 --> 01:17:58,840
who believed in me
from the beginning.

1357
01:17:58,924 --> 01:18:02,635
Oh, Horton.
We're going to miss you.

1358
01:18:02,720 --> 01:18:04,346
Gee.

1359
01:18:04,430 --> 01:18:06,681
What are we gonna do
without you, Horton?

1360
01:18:06,766 --> 01:18:10,894
Aw, don't worry.
I'll always be around.

1361
01:18:10,978 --> 01:18:13,855
♪ And even as I wander♪

1362
01:18:13,939 --> 01:18:16,316
♪ l'm keeping you in sight ♪

1363
01:18:16,400 --> 01:18:19,152
♪ You're a candle in the window ♪

1364
01:18:19,236 --> 01:18:22,447
- ♪ On a cold, dark winter's night ♪
- Beautiful metaphor.

1365
01:18:22,531 --> 01:18:24,866
♪ And I'm getting closer♪

1366
01:18:24,950 --> 01:18:29,704
♪ Than I ever thought I might ♪

1367
01:18:29,789 --> 01:18:32,457
Whoo! That's a little high for me.

1368
01:18:32,541 --> 01:18:37,962
- ♪ Baby, I can't fight this ♪
- ♪ Feeling anymore ♪

1369
01:18:38,047 --> 01:18:42,509
♪ I've forgotten
what I started fightin' for♪

1370
01:18:42,593 --> 01:18:44,803
Ahh.

1371
01:18:44,887 --> 01:18:48,139
♪ And if I have to crawl
upon your floor ♪

1372
01:18:48,224 --> 01:18:50,892
♪ Come crashing
through your door♪

1373
01:18:50,976 --> 01:18:53,937
♪ Baby, l can't fight
this feeling anymore ♪

1374
01:18:54,021 --> 01:18:56,773
♪ l can't fight this feeling ♪

1375
01:18:56,857 --> 01:19:00,068
- ♪ Anymore ♪
- Whoo!

1377
01:19:05,282 --> 01:19:07,700
And so all ended well...

1378
01:19:07,785 --> 01:19:09,786
for both Horton and Whos...

1379
01:19:09,870 --> 01:19:13,289
and for all in thejungle,
even kangaroos.

1380
01:19:13,374 --> 01:19:16,668
So let that be a lesson
to one and to all.

1381
01:19:16,752 --> 01:19:21,506
A person's a person,
no matter how small.

1382
01:19:26,137 --> 01:19:28,138
Ahh.
